DATA & PRIVACY — PLAIN LANGUAGE STATEMENT

This software is designed with one principle: your data belongs to you.

  · Nothing you log is ever sent to the developer or any third party.
  · The app stores all your notes and entries on your own device (localStorage).
  · No analytics, no tracking scripts, no advertising infrastructure exists
    in this code. There is nothing to sell and no one collecting it.
  · Optional cross-device sync, if enabled, uses a Firebase project that YOU
    configure with YOUR own account. The developer never has access to it.
  · Payment processing (if used) goes through Razorpay. The developer
    receives only the payment notification — not your card details.

You are safe to use this app as a private journal. The code is open so you
can verify these claims yourself.

